The '''Chukyo Metropolis proposal'''s (中京都構想 and [[:ja:岐阜愛知新首都構想]]) are proposed transformations of the [[Aichi prefecture]] into a metropolis.<ref>[http://www.asahi.com/politics/update/1206/TKY201012060358.html 愛知知事選、大村議員が出馬表明 河村市長と連携掲げる] 朝日新聞 - 2010/12/06</ref> Aichi's prefectural governor, Mr. Omura, formed [[:ja:中京維新の会]] ''Chukyo Isshin no Kai'' or [[Chukyo Metropolitan Area]] Renewal Association in 2012.<ref>http://www.asahi.com/articles/ASH5L36FHH5LOIPE004.html</ref> The latter plan is an alternate that also incorporates [[Gifu prefecture]] in the Metropolis.
[[File:Government squashing.png|thumb|left|250px|The above figure explains the generic process of Metropolis creation in Japan, a model which has extensive basis in East Asian administrative history.]] The metropolis would require [[Nagoya]] city to be dissolved and reorganized into wards under metropolitan authority. The concept has parallels with [[History of Tokyo#Dissolution of Tokyo City|Tokyo]]'s past and [[Osaka Metropolis plan|Osaka's proposed reorganization]].
