The '''Malino II Accord''' was signed on 13 February 2002 as a settlement between warring parties in the [[Maluku sectarian conflict]] that commenced in 1999 in the [[Maluku Islands]] of [[Indonesia]].<ref>''Laskar Jihad'' by [[Noorhaidi Hasan]] p209</ref> (February 12 according to the [[UK]]'s [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]]).<ref>[http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-the-fco/country-profiles/asia-oceania/indonesia/?profile=all UK FCO] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090705083941/http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-the-fco/country-profiles/asia-oceania/indonesia/?profile=all |date=2009-07-05 }}</ref>
It was signed in the [[Sulawesi]] town of [[Malino, Indonesia|Malino]].
